body:
@pallavi-rao For export, <fields> needs to go because it is superfluous. The list of fields that gets exported to database is determined by the target table definition. If the target table definition has 3 fields, then only 3 fields from the HDFS will be exported. 

For import, we need the fields explicitly specified by the user. 

The way this is implemented now is to do a check in the EntityParser to validate the Export does not have <fields> tag.
